"script": "Over your lifetime, you'll produce around 25,000 liters of saliva. That's enough spit to fill two backyard swimming pools right up to the brim. Every single day, the glands in your mouth quietly pump out about a liter and a half, mostly while you eat and sleep. You see, saliva is always working, breaking down your food and shielding your teeth from decay. And it never really stops, even when your mouth feels bone dry. So by the time you're old, you've made enough drool to float a small boat, and you swallowed nearly every drop without ever noticing.",
